{"title_page": "June-Young Soh", "text_new": "{{Korean name|[[So (Korean name)|Soh]]}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = June-Young Soh\n| image              = June-Young Soh.jpg\n| alt                = Image of June-Young Soh\n| caption            = Image of June-Young Soh\n| native_name        = June-Young Soh\n| native_name_lang   = kr\n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1965|1|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = South Korean\n| citizenship        = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = \n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = <!-- Discouraged in most cases, specifically when promotional, and requiring a reliable source -->\n| known_for          = [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCbx8xxbHJm8kaSlc8WdRu9g?view_as=subscriber/ The Lost Garden]\n| notable_works      = <!-- produces label \"Notable work\"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label \"Notable credit(s)\"; or by |works=, which produces label \"Works\" -->\n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\"  or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight             = <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| religion           = <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source; do not add a religious denomination here -->\n| denomination       = <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| spouse             = <!-- Use article title or common name -->\n| partner            = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = <!-- overrides mother and father parameters -->\n| mother             = <!-- may be used (optionally with father parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| father             = <!-- may be used (optionally with mother parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| relatives          = \n| family             = \n| awards             = \n| website            = <!-- {{https://www.facebook.com/juneyoung.soh}} -->\n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n| module             = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| hangul             = {{linktext|\uc18c|\uc900|\uc601}}\n| hanja              = !\n| mr                 = So Chuny\u014fng\n| rr                 = So Jun-yeong}}\n}}\n'''June-Young Soh''' (born 15 January 1965) is a South Korean director/musician who made his worldwide debut<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/782887.shtml|title=Back to the lost garden - Global Times|publisher=}}</ref> in Shanghai [[Mercedes-Benz Arena (Shanghai)|Mercedes-Benz Arena]] with the musical [http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/782887.shtml ''The Lost Garden'' on 8 June 2013]. His current work, [https://www.facebook.com/thechasa/ 'CHASA'], is a circus based musical the story of which was derived from the old Korean myth; '[[Chasa Bonpuri]]'.\n\nBorn and raised in Seoul, he became involved in rock music as a teenager; experiences in his first band, 'Since & Hence', has led him to become a professional musician in the later years. He became a professor at [[Seoul Institute of the Arts]] in his late 20s and released his first album with [https://www.warnermusic.co.kr/ Warner Music Korea] in 1993. It was not until 1996, he released his second album with [https://www.sonymusic.co.kr/ Sony Music Korea]. He released his third album, [https://www.amazon.com/%ED%8C%8C%EB%9D%BC%EB%8B%A4%EC%9D%B4%EC%8A%A4-Paradise-Market-June-Young-Soh/dp/B06Y5MB33K 'The paradise market'] in April 2017.\n\nHe was involved in a number of exhibition productions earlier in his career including [[Taej\u014fn Expo '93]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1993122800329120007&edtNo=15&printCount=1&publishDate=1993-12-28&officeId=00032&pageNo=20&printNo=14957&publishType=00010|title=\uc2e0\uc778\uac00\uc218\ub4e4 \uc2e0\uace1\uacbd\uc7c1; \uc18c\uc900\uc601\u00b7\ud64d\uc9c0\uc218\ub4f1 \uc18d\uc18d\uc568\ubc94\ub0b4 \ub0b4\ub144\ub3cc\ud48d \uc608\uace0|work=[[Kyunghyang Shinmun]]|date=28 December 1993|accessdate=13 May 2016}}</ref> and [[Expo '98]] where he worked as the composer/sound director of the main film of the pavilion. He established his 3D surround sound technics working in the pavilion environments during those early years. He further developed his ideas of 3D sound when he became the director of music and sound for the Korean pavilion of the Lisbon World Expo in 1998. He tested 12.3 surround sound in the main film of the pavilion, 'Pearl Sea' which was an underwater story of a woman diver for pearls.\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.facebook.com/TheLostGardenMusical/ The Lost Garden]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Soh, June-Young}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Seoul]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=May 2016}}\n{{Korean name|[[So (Korean name)|Soh]]}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = June-Young Soh\n| image              = June-Young Soh.jpg\n| alt                = Image of June-Young Soh\n| caption            = Image of June-Young Soh\n| native_name        = June-Young Soh\n| native_name_lang   = kr\n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1965|1|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = South Korean\n| citizenship        = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = \n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = <!-- Discouraged in most cases, specifically when promotional, and requiring a reliable source -->\n| known_for          = [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCbx8xxbHJm8kaSlc8WdRu9g?view_as=subscriber/ The Lost Garden]\n| notable_works      = <!-- produces label \"Notable work\"; may be overridden by |credits=, which produces label \"Notable credit(s)\"; or by |works=, which produces label \"Works\" -->\n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\"  or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight             = <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| religion           = <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source; do not add a religious denomination here -->\n| denomination       = <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| spouse             = <!-- Use article title or common name -->\n| partner            = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = <!-- overrides mother and father parameters -->\n| mother             = <!-- may be used (optionally with father parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| father             = <!-- may be used (optionally with mother parameter) in place of parents parameter (displays \"Parent(s)\" as label) -->\n| relatives          = \n| family             = \n| awards             = \n| website            = <!-- {{https://www.facebook.com/juneyoung.soh}} -->\n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n| module             = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| hangul             = {{linktext|\uc18c|\uc900|\uc601}}\n| hanja              = !\n| mr                 = So Chuny\u014fng\n| rr                 = So Jun-yeong}}\n}}\n'''June-Young Soh''' (born 15 January 1965) is a South Korean director/musician who made his worldwide debut<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/782887.shtml|title=Back to the lost garden - Global Times|publisher=}}</ref> in Shanghai [[Mercedes-Benz Arena (Shanghai)|Mercedes-Benz Arena]] with the musical [http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/782887.shtml ''The Lost Garden'' on 8 June 2013]. His current work, [https://www.facebook.com/thechasa/ 'CHASA'], is a circus based musical the story of which was derived from the old Korean myth; '[[Chasa Bonpuri]]'.\n\nBorn and raised in Seoul, he became involved in rock music as a teenager; experiences in his first band, 'Since & Hence', has led him to become a professional musician in the later years. He became a professor at [[Seoul Institute of the Arts]] in his late 20s and released his first album with [https://www.warnermusic.co.kr/ Warner Music Korea] in 1993. It was not until 1996, he released his second album with [https://www.sonymusic.co.kr/ Sony Music Korea]. He released his third album, [https://www.amazon.com/%ED%8C%8C%EB%9D%BC%EB%8B%A4%EC%9D%B4%EC%8A%A4-Paradise-Market-June-Young-Soh/dp/B06Y5MB33K 'The paradise market'] in April 2017.\n\nHe was involved in a number of exhibition productions earlier in his career including [[Taej\u014fn Expo '93]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1993122800329120007&edtNo=15&printCount=1&publishDate=1993-12-28&officeId=00032&pageNo=20&printNo=14957&publishType=00010|title=\uc2e0\uc778\uac00\uc218\ub4e4 \uc2e0\uace1\uacbd\uc7c1; \uc18c\uc900\uc601\u00b7\ud64d\uc9c0\uc218\ub4f1 \uc18d\uc18d\uc568\ubc94\ub0b4 \ub0b4\ub144\ub3cc\ud48d \uc608\uace0|work=[[Kyunghyang Shinmun]]|date=28 December 1993|accessdate=13 May 2016}}</ref> and [[Expo '98]] where he worked as the composer/sound director of the main film of the pavilion. He established his 3D surround sound technics working in the pavilion environments during those early years. He further developed his ideas of 3D sound when he became the director of music and sound for the Korean pavilion of the Lisbon World Expo in 1998. He tested 12.3 surround sound in the main film of the pavilion, 'Pearl Sea' which was an underwater story of a woman diver for pearls.\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.facebook.com/TheLostGardenMusical/ The Lost Garden]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Soh, June-Young}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Seoul]]\n", "name_user": "Playjune", "label": "safe", "comment": "removed a box", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/June-Young_Soh"}
