, and on the morning show ''Good Day Atlanta''. In 2007, the orchestra performed in Washington D.C. at the World War II Memorial.{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}\n\n==Notable alumni==\n\n* [[EJay Day]] - singer-songwriter; top 10 finalist in the original season of [[American Idol (season 1)|American Idol]]; collaborator and songwriter for pop artists\n* [[Jonathan Massaquoi]] - football player; played [[college football]] for the [[Troy Trojans football|Troy University Trojans]] and in the [[NFL]] for the [[Atlanta Falcons]]\n* [[Ted Roof]] - assistant football coach at [[Georgia Tech]]; former head football coach at [[Duke University]]; football player for Georgia Tech\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://centralgwinnett.net/ Central Gwinnett High School website]\n* [http://gwinnett.k12.ga.us/ Gwinnett County Public Schools website]\n{{Gwinnett County, Georgia Schools}}\n{{GHSA Class AAAAAA Region 8}}\n\n[[Category:Public high schools in Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n[[Category:Schools in Gwinnett County, Georgia]]\n[[Category:1957 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1957]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n| name = Central Gwinnett High School \n| image = Cental Gwinnett crest2.jpg\n| image_size = 220\n| motto =\"The Best School In America\" \n| coordinates = {{Coord|33.95058|-83.99945|type:edu_region:US-GA|display=title}}\n| type = High school (grades 9 - 12)\n| established = 1957 <ref name=AbouttheSchool>{{cite web|title=About the School|url=http://www.centralgwinnett.net/?PageName=%27AboutTheSchool%27|publisher=Central Gwinnett High School|accessdate=3 November 2015}}</ref>\n| principal = Shane Orr\n| campus = Suburban\n| enrolment = \t2,170<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_detail.asp?Search=1&DistrictID=1302550&SchoolPageNum=2&ID=130255001129|title=Central Gwinnett High School|publisher=National Center for Education Statistics|accessdate=November 6, 